comments: Towns (MIN) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Allen (CLE) prior to incidental arm contact occurring.
Allen's (CLE) left foot is out of bounds when he is in possession of the ball.  Possession is correctly awarded to Minnesota.
Goodwin (CLE) briefly grasps Russell's (MIN) jersey and marginal contact occurs during the inbound.
Goodwin (CLE) briefly has his arm around Towns' (MIN) left leg before immediately removing his arm as he moves over the pick.
Goodwin (CLE) and Beverley (MIN) make incidental foot to foot contact with one another on the perimeter.
Beverley (MIN) moves forward toward Goodwin (CLE) and marginal contact occurs to Goodwin's side as he makes the pass.
Okoro (CLE) extends his arm in pursuit of the rebound and incidental contact occurs with Beverley's (MIN) left arm after the ball has been deflected away by Edwards (MIN).
Towns (MIN) is already in Okoro's (CLE) path and is firming up when contact occurs.

Goodwin (CLE) brushes Edwards' (MIN) right arm and marginal contact occurs at the end of Edwards' drive. Allen (CLE) maintains a rested forearm on Edwards' side and marginal contact occurs as Edwards passes thereafter.
Beverley (MIN) commits a take foul on Osman (CLE) after Osman's gather. After communicating with the Replay Center, it was determined that the contact did not meet the criteria for a clear path foul.
Vanderbilt (MIN) extends his arm in pursuit of the rebound and marginal contact occurs with Mobley (CLE) as Mobley attempts to back-tap the ball.
Towns (MIN) establishes a wide screening position in Goodwin's (CLE) path and contact occurs to his foot.
Goodwin (CLE) extends his arm into Russell's (MIN) path and initiates contact prior to the start of Russell's upward shooting motion.
Beverley (MIN) rests his forearm on Osman's (CLE) side and marginal contact occurs as Osman drives toward the lane.
Vanderbilt (MIN) legally contests Mobley's (CLE) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Osman (CLE) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Beverley (MIN) during rebounding.

Beverley (MIN) briefly grasps and then quickly releases Okoro's (CLE) jersey near the free throw line. Beverley then dives to the floor and incidental body contact occurs with Okoro as Beverley ties up Okoro.  A jump ball is correctly called.

After making initial incidental arm contact with one another, Edwards (MIN) is retreating behind Okoro (CLE) when Edwards' leg makes incidental contact with the back of Okoro's head. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Edwards (MIN) legally contests Osman's (CLE) jump shot attempt.
Towns (MIN) is firming up over his right leg and absorbs the contact from Goodwin (CLE) during the pick.
Towns (MIN) and Goodwin (CLE) briefly engage and disengage off ball.
Towns (MIN) briefly grasps and then quickly releases Osman's (CLE) left arm off-ball.
Osman (CLE) brings his off-arm toward Vanderbilt's (MIN) front and marginal contact occurs as Osman releases away toward the wing.
Vanderbilt (MIN) legally contests Osman's (CLE) jump shot attempt.
Osman (CLE) does not overtly extend his leg to create contact with Vanderbilt (MIN) when he leans forward and the leg to leg contact during his shooting motion is marginal.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: Replay review of the out of bounds call on MIN pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Mobley (CLE) does not re-establish in bounds before making contact with the ball. After communicating with the Replay Center, the game clock was set to 04.6.
Towns (MIN) establishes himself in a screening position from a wide stance and marginal contact occurs with Goodwin (CLE), who moves through the contact to continue play.
Goodwin (CLE) commits a take foul on Russell (MIN).
Beverley (MIN) makes clean contact with the ball during Goodwin's (CLE) upward shooting motion and legally contests his jump shot attempt.
